articles.description: Ohio State and Michigan will play a big game late in the season with Big Ten title implications at stake.
articles.headline: No. 8 Ohio State visits No. 22 Michigan

articles.description: Cassius Winston scored 17 points, and No. 2 Michigan State erased a 27-point deficit on Saturday to beat Northwestern 65-60 and extend its winning streak to 10 games.
articles.headline: No. 2 Michigan St. rallies from 27 down, beats Northwestern

images.caption: Cassius Winston gets the ball at the top of the arc and drains a cold-blooded triple as Michigan State takes a 4-point lead over Northwestern in an eventual 65-60 win.
images.name: Clutch Winston 3-pointer cements Spartan comeback

articles.description: Tremont Waters made a shot in the lane with 19 seconds remaining in the game to give LSU a 64-63 Southeastern Conference victory against Missouri on Saturday.
articles.headline: Waters' field goal gives LSU 64-63 win over Missouri

articles.description: PJ Washington scored 16 points, Kevin Knox added 13, and Kentucky beat Alabama 81-71 on Saturday to end a four-game slide.
articles.headline: Kentucky beats Alabama 81-71 behind Washington's 16 points

images.caption: Alabama's John Petty drives to the paint and delivers a lob to Donta Hall, who throws down a thunderous one-handed alley-oop dunk.
images.name: Hall reaches back for emphatic alley-oop

articles.description: Alex Petrie scored 27 points and E.J. Stephens scored 16 with six assists and three rebounds and Lafayette pulled away from American with a 90-83 win on Saturday.
articles.headline: Lafayette pulls away from American 90-83 behind Petrie

articles.description: Trae Young scores 26 points but Mohamed Bamba counters with 10 points and 18 rebounds in the Longhorns' 77-66 victory over the Sooners.
articles.headline: Texas hands Oklahoma fifth straight loss

images.caption: Trae Young scores 26 points but Mohamed Bamba counters with 10 points and 18 rebounds in the Longhorns' 77-66 victory over the Sooners.
